**Trading Comparables**

The comps universe includes Amazon, Costco, Target, Kroger, and Dollar General. We exclude Amazon and Costco from the peer median. Amazon's retail multiples are inflated by AWS, and Costco trades on a membership premium that is structurally different from Walmart's format. The remaining three peers trade at 7.6x to 9.9x EV/EBITDA. We use an adjusted peer median of 9.85x applied to FY2027E EBITDA.

This gives a comps-implied value of $65.38 per share. We weight this at 30% in the blend, not the standard 50%, because the peer set does not fully capture Walmart's evolving revenue mix. A pure retailer multiple undersells the advertising and membership economics.

