**Catalysts and Risks**

| **Catalysts** | **Key Risks** |
| --- | --- |
| Walmart Connect crosses $5B in revenue ahead of schedule | Amazon accelerates grocery and retail investment, compressing Walmart's pricing power |
| Walmart+ subscriber count surpasses 50M, proving the membership flywheel works | Consumer trade-down reverses as macro improves, reducing the Walmart traffic tailwind |
| Operating margin prints above 4.5% for two consecutive quarters | Advertising growth slows if brand budgets shift to social media platforms |
| Fulfillment-as-a-service revenue gets called out separately in earnings | Cost overruns or weak ROI on the fulfillment center buildout |
| Capex guidance starts declining, confirming the investment cycle is peaking | Regulatory pressure on data usage for Walmart Connect ad targeting |

